<p>Your <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30521257/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">shoulders </a>are primary upper body muscles that contribute to a well-developed and balanced physique. They are active in multiple daily movements involving rotating and moving your arms up and across your body. Some include lifting heavy objects, carrying large boxes, throwing balls, and reaching across your body. </p>



<p>There are many <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/training/benefits-of-push-ups" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">benefits of push-ups</a> including increasing shoulder strength and stability. They contribute to improved upper-body functional performance, tone the shoulders and upper arms, and enhance joint stability and flexibility. </p>



<p>These push-ups for shoulders utilize a <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4592763/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">compound approach</a> by targeting multiple muscle groups. They activate the chest, upper arms, and shoulders for a comprehensive, balanced upper-body workout.</p>



<p>Read on to discover seven push-up variations for the best shoulder workout, each with a unique and targeted approach. You will find descriptive instructions for executing each exercise, including tips on muscle engagement and benefits.</p>



<div class="wp-block-group ft-snippet is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<p class="has-medium-font-size">7 Push Ups Variations For Shoulders</p>



<p>Read on for guidance on the best push-up variations for targeting your shoulders. These will optimize your upper-body routine.</p>



<ul>
<li><a href="#Pike-Push-Ups">Pike Push-Ups.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Handstand-Push-Ups">Handstand Push-Ups.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Decline-Pike-Push-Ups">Decline Pike Push-Ups. </a></li>



<li><a href="#Reverse-Iron-Cross-Push-Ups">Reverse Iron Cross Push-Ups.</a></li>



<li><a href="#T-Push-Ups">T Push-Ups.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Spider-Push-Ups">Spider Push-Ups.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Hindu-Push-Ups">Hindu Push-Ups.</a></li>
</ul>



<p>They work for a variety of workout goals and fitness levels and can be customized as needed. Feel free to program these push-ups for shoulders into your routine based on preference and training goals.</p>
</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">7 Push Ups Variations To Building Shoulder Strength</h2>



<p>The following exercises strengthen your shoulders and surrounding muscles for an effective and comprehensive stimulus. You can perform them as listed or based on training goals and preferences.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Pike-Push-Ups">Pike Push-Ups</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/pike-push-up" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Pike push-ups</a> offer a unique variation from the traditional push-up. It involves performing the classic movement with your hips raised rather than in a plank position. It follows a straightforward movement, making it a beneficial option in <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/shoulder-workouts-for-beginners" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">shoulder workouts for beginners</a>.</p>



<p>This workout emphasizes the shoulders and triceps due to the heightened stance of the hips. Keeping your arms closer to your body engages the core and enhances shoulder strength and stability.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Pike Push-Ups" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/980233068?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Pike Push-Up Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How to do</h4>



<ol>
<li>This workout can be performed at home or in a gym. Find a mat or comfortable padded area.</li>



<li>Start in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders. The balls of your feet should be on the ground.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core.</li>



<li>Raise your hips and walk your hands back until you are in a downward dog position. Keep your arms and legs straight.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Flex your elbows and lower your head down to the floor. Pause at the bottom and squeeze your shoulder blades together.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Exhale as you push your body back up to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired number of repetitions and sets.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Don’t round the shoulders or back during the movement. Focus on keeping your back straight to avoid straining the spine.</li>



<li>Use slow and controlled movements during the lowering and pushing-up phases.</li>



<li>Engage your core throughout the movement. This helps to keep your hips up and limits lower back stress.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Avoid tucking your head into your chest or lifting your head. This decreases the chance of neck strain and injury.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<figure class="wp-block-table table-custom h-title table-border" style="font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-weight:500"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Training Style</p></th><th class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"><p class="pri-color-1">Sets</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Reps</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Strength Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">4–6</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Hypertrophy</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">8–10</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Endurance Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">12–15</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Power Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">1–3 (Explosive)</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps of Pike Push-Ups</figcaption></figure>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Handstand-Push-Ups">Handstand Push-Ups</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/handstand-push-up" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Handstand push-ups</a> are a challenging exercise that isolates the shoulders for increased intensity and muscle building. They involve performing the traditional push-up while in a handstand position. Maintaining proper form requires additional skill, and thus, beginners should obtain assistance from a fitness professional before attempting them.</p>



<p>This exercise offers many benefits, including versatility, as it can be performed anywhere and requires no equipment. It also enhances balance, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5611901/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">stability</a>, and coordination to maintain the handstand position. By activating all three shoulder muscle heads, it provides a well-rounded approach to targeting the shoulders.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Handstand Push-Up" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1008682697?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Handstand Push-Up Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Set up a mat in front of a sturdy wall in a large open space.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Face away from the wall with your feet hip-width apart, about 10 inches from the wall.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Bend down and place your hands on the ground in front of you. Kick one leg back onto the wall, followed by the other leg.</li>



<li>Slowly bring your hands back while walking up the wall with your legs. Do this until your hands are several inches away from the wall with your legs straight up.</li>



<li>With your arms fully extended, exhale and flex your elbows to lower your head to the floor. Pause briefly at the bottom and squeeze your shoulder blades together.</li>



<li>Inhale and extend your elbows to push back up to the starting position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired number of reps and sets.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Before attempting this exercise, ensure that you can get into a handstand position. If needed, enlist the help of a fitness professional for spotting assistance.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Perform a suitable <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5833972/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">warm-up</a> before handstand push-ups. This should include dynamic shoulder stretches to increase blood flow and oxygen delivery to the working muscles.</li>



<li>Execute each repetition using slow, controlled movements. This allows you to maintain balance without falling over and ensures targeted muscle activation.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<figure class="wp-block-table table-custom h-title table-border" style="font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-weight:500"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Training Style</p></th><th class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"><p class="pri-color-1">Sets</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Reps</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Strength Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">4–6</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Hypertrophy</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">8–10</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Endurance Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">12+</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Power Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">1–3 (Explosive)</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps of Handstand Push-Ups</figcaption></figure>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Decline-Pike-Push-Ups">Decline Pike Push-Ups</h3>



<p>We’ve already discussed the pike push-up, but the decline pike push-up takes it a step further. It elevates your feet to add even more intensity to the shoulder muscles. This also targets the upper chest and <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5827912/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">triceps muscles</a>.</p>



<p>This movement is challenging but effective and offers many benefits. These include improved upper-body symmetry, increased shoulder mobility, and enhanced coordination and balance.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Decline Pike Push-Up" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1013439206?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Decline Pike Push-Ups Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand in front of a sturdy bench. Ensure it’s at a height that allows you to raise your legs. Make sure you’re able to extend them against the raised surface.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Kneel down with your hands directly below your shoulders and extend your arms. Kick both feet back, bringing them onto the bench.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Raise your hips and walk your hands back until you are in a V position. The balls of your feet should be on the bench with your arms and legs straight.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Flex your elbows and lower your head down to the floor. Pause at the bottom and squeeze your shoulder blades together.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Exhale as you push your body back up to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired number of repetitions and sets.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Ensure the raised surface is set at a suitable height. This allows you to keep the correct form.</li>



<li>Avoid flaring your elbows out to the sides to keep targeted muscle activation.</li>



<li>Concentrate on squeezing the shoulder blades together using controlled movements to maximize muscle activation.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps</h4>



