<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Reverse-Iron-Cross-Push-Ups">Reverse Iron Cross Push-Ups</h3>



<p>The reverse iron cross push-up takes a very different approach from the traditional push-up, as you perform it on your back. This creates a unique challenge targeting the rear deltoids, which are often overlooked in traditional shoulder workouts. This exercise creates a different stimulus for a well-rounded workout.</p>



<p>This exercise has many benefits including increasing strength and definition in the shoulders and upper back. It is an effective part of a pull-day routine with cable rows or pull-ups for an increased shoulder focus. It is also extremely versatile and can be a beneficial part of your <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/at-home-shoulder-workout" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">at home shoulder workouts</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Reverse Iron Cross Push-Ups" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/986290719?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Reverse Iron Cross Push-Ups Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Lie on your back with your feet flat on the ground, shoulder-width apart, and knees bent.</li>



<li>Extend your arms out to your sides to form a ‘T’ shape. Your elbows should be flexed at 90 degrees.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core.</li>



<li>Exhale as you engage your shoulders and upper back to raise your chest off the ground.</li>



<li>Raise your upper back enough so your elbows clear the floor.</li>



<li>Hold this position for a count.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Slowly return back to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired number of reps and sets.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your gaze in front of you, and avoid bending or tucking the head. This prevents straining the neck.</li>



<li>Keep your core engaged throughout and maintain slow and controlled movements.</li>



<li>Focus on proper breathing techniques. Inhale to engage your core and exhale as you raise your chest up.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



