<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="T-Push-Ups">T Push-Ups</h3>



<p>The T push-up resembles the traditional push-up with an additional step to rotate and lift each arm at the end. It targets your chest, shoulders, and upper arms and requires increased focus on coordination during the rotation phase.</p>



<p>This exercise has many benefits, including improving the shoulder joint stability required to rotate and extend the arm. It creates a gentle stretch to the shoulder joint, which improves flexibility and <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8067745/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">range of motion</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="T Push-Up" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/980245849?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">T Push-Ups Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Start in a traditional push-up plank position. Your hands should be under or slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, and your feet should be together.</li>



<li>Inhale to engage your core.</li>



<li>Lower your chest towards the ground, keeping your core engaged and your back straight.</li>



<li>Pause at the bottom before pushing back up to a plank.</li>



<li>Continue engaging the core, and lift one arm off the ground. Rotate your body to reach your arm up toward the ceiling, forming a <em>T </em>shape.</li>



<li>Hold this position for a moment, squeezing the shoulders and triceps.</li>



<li>Exhale as you return your arm to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat the movement on the other side.</li>



<li>Continue for the desired number of reps and sets.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Do not splay your elbows out to the side, as this creates stress on the shoulder joint.</li>



<li>Keep your core engaged and your back in a neutral position to protect the lower back.</li>



<li>Focus on using slow and controlled movements to activate the target muscles optimally.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



