<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Spider-Push-Ups">Spider Push-Ups</h3>



<p>The spider push-up requires increased coordination due to its dynamic approach, which targets both upper and lower body muscles. Its name comes from the crawling motion required to perform the exercise properly.&nbsp;</p>



<p>As mentioned, this compound movement targets all major muscle groups, including shoulders, chest, glutes, quads, and hamstrings. It also elicits core activation to keep the torso steady and the lower back aligned throughout the movement.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Spider Push-up" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/982320157?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Spider Push-Ups Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Start in a plank position on a mat or padded floor. Your hands should be directly under your shoulders.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Ensure you’re on the balls of your feet with both legs extended.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Flex your elbows to lower your chest to the floor.</li>



<li>Exhale, and as you lower down, drive one knee up along the side of your body.</li>



<li>Inhale and pause for a second, engaging your core and upper body.</li>



<li>Exhale and bring your knee back behind you.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Extend your elbows to push back up to the plank starting position.</li>



<li>Perform the same movement with the other knee.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired reps and sets.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Ensure your arms and knees work in sync throughout each repetition to maintain balance and stability.</li>



<li>Keep your elbows tucked in as you drive your knees up. This increases the focus on the shoulder muscles for maximum activation.</li>



<li>Don’t rush through the motions. Perform each movement slowly and with control to achieve the best benefits.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



