<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Hindu-Push-Ups">Hindu Push-Ups</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/hindu-push-up" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Hindu push-up</a> is an advanced variation that combines the push-up and overhead press exercises. Its dynamic motion also resembles the downward dog yoga pose. </p>



<p>This challenging exercise requires you to push through an inverted V-shape, bringing your head through your arms. It primarily targets the chest and shoulders, with secondary activation from the core, triceps, glutes, and hamstrings. It also provides a gentle stretch to the abdominals.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Hindu Push-Up" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1008435692?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Hindu Push-Ups Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Start in a kneeling position on a mat or padded floor. Your hands should be directly under your shoulders, facing slightly outward.</li>



<li>Bring both legs back to come onto your toes. At the same time, walk your hands back until your torso is in an inverted V-shape.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Exhale and bring your head down to the floor while flexing your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together.</li>



<li>Continue the motion to bring your head between your arms and lift your chest up.</li>



<li>Pause briefly in this final position, focusing on squeezing the shoulder blades together.</li>



<li>Inhale and flex your shoulders to bring your upper body back down and through your arms.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Exhale as you extend your elbows, pushing back up to the inverted V shape to complete the movement.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired number of reps and sets.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Ensure to keep <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8310485/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">controlled movements</a> throughout the exercise. Don’t use momentum to complete the motion.</li>



<li>Keep your arms at shoulder-width with your hands slightly pointing outwards. This increases targeted muscle activation and reduces potential wrist stress.</li>



<li>Avoid tucking or straining your neck throughout the movement. This could result in neck or spinal injury.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



