<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Anatomy Of The Shoulders</h2>



<p>The <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30521257/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">shoulder musculature</a> is extensive and made up of multiple groupings including the rotator cuff, serratus anterior, and deltoid muscles. </p>



<p>The shoulder muscles are prime movers in many functional activities, such as lifting objects, pulling doors open, and carrying groceries. These exercises strengthen the shoulders and surrounding upper-body muscles for improved functional performance in many areas of daily life.</p>



<p>Studies have found that the shoulder muscles can reach <a href="https://content.iospress.com/articles/journal-of-back-and-musculoskeletal-rehabilitation/bmr191771" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">40%–50%</a> of maximum voluntary contraction during push-up exercises. This demonstrates the effectiveness of push-up variations in targeting the shoulder muscles. </p>


